# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Finwise — Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env.local (in this same client/ folder) and fill in values.
# You can also use a .env.local at the repository root; client/ values win if both exist.
# Find these in: Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API
#
# If Supabase "Connect" gave Next.js names, you can paste them as-is — Vite maps them in:
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL  → same as VITE_SUPABASE_URL
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY → same as VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Your project URL — looks like https://xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co

# Client API key — safe to expose in the browser (RLS still applies):
#   • New projects: "Publishable" key (sb_publishable_…) from Dashboard → Settings → API
#   • Legacy: "anon" / "public" JWT (long string starting with eyJ…)
# Never put sb_secret_… or the service_role JWT here — those are for trusted servers only.
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-publishable-or-legacy-anon-key

# Plaid runs on the Node API (repo root `npm run dev`). Configure Plaid + SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
# in server/.env — see server/.env.example. The Vite dev server proxies /api to that server.
